summary_en:
Difficult to say what happened. Reports suggest that Syrian government airstrike on Kafr Takharim and/or Salqin (they're neighboring villages) contained some sort of toxic substance, possibly arsenic (according to a tweet). Sources reported the substance dropped was soft and light like cotton or spiderwebs. A few videos relate to the incident, but they don't show much. One focuses on white material in a tree, but it's difficult to tell what it is. Another (allegedly) shows announcements on minarets warning residents not to touch the white substance in the streets. Another video shows a helicopter flying, but it's unclear if this was the aircraft that carried out the CW attack. Another video focuses on a white cloud in the sky, but again, it's unclear whether that relates to the CW attack. One last video shows a weapon close up, but it's unclear to me whether it's related to the incident. Arabic speakers should listen to the videos to get additional details. 
Note: Based on time of social media posts, date of attack was Oct 13, 2012, rather than Oct 14, as the French Foreign Ministry reported. The first post about the incident was around 15:30 (Syria time) on Oct 13. 
Note: Reports say the attack was on both Kafr Takharim and Salqin, and videos appear to come from both towns. Location entered on spreadsheet is for Kafr Takharim (because I had to choose one), but this may have occured in Salqin or in between the towns.
collections.2: Civilian casualties as a result of alleged attacks by syrian goverment forces
cid.title_en: Chemical attack in Kafr Takharim or Salqin, Idlib

summary_en: I could not find any sources reporting a CW attack in Harasta on or around 19 Nov 2012 (and no videos on the "Master" tab are identified as realting to this incident). I searched with just the term "حرستا" for Nov 17 - 23, 2012 on twitter, and nothing came up related to chemical weapons, toxic gasses, etc.

Two videos on the "master" tab show numerous patients being treated in a small hospital. Most patients are being treated with oxygen masks, and some have had their clothes removed, which is consistent with treatment for exposure to a chemical weapon. One of the videos reports that the chemical weapon was a nerve agent, however patients in the hospital do not appear to show symptoms that are trademarks of exposure to nerve agents, such as convulsions/seizures, foaming at the mouth, or pinpoint pupils. Their symptoms (evidently choking and difficulty breathing) are more consistent with exposure to a choking agent. However there is no difinitive way to identify this from these videos. There is a good deal of spoken material in both videos, thus it would be worth having an arabic speaker listen to them to see what other details could be understood from the videos' audio. 
Another video found on twitter (listed on the discovery tab) shows a close-up of another patient being treated in the hospital - consistent with the other two videos. 
Eighte other videos posted by "homs live" show close-ups of individuals who allegedly were killed in the attack, by exposure to the chemical weapon. (All are listed in the discovery tab.)
Note: sources on twitter reported the attack was in al Khalidiya and al Bayada - two neighborhoods right next to each other in Homs, thus it's unclear exactly where the attack happened.
First tweets posted around 20:45 Syria time on 23 Dec 2012.

summary_en: Not a lot of information about what happened. According to the White Helmets twitter page (@SyriaCivilDef) there were reports of a chemical attack in Jabal Zawiya, Idlib at 22:00 on 26 April 2015. Barrel bombs were used to drop the toxic substances (allegedly chlorine). Although there weren’t many videos available, the channel عبدالله جدعان posted many videos presumably of the aftermath of the attacks. ٍٍReports claim that 9 were found dead as a result of the attack, of which 4 were children. Several videos show buildings in ruins and bulldozers cleaning up. Witnesses recall seeing planes drop the barrel bombs, which contained the toxic substances. Another video shows what may be a funeral procession the day after the attack, with a group of men carrying two bodies.
cid.title_en: Chemical attack in the village of Joseph in Jabal al-Zawiya, Idlib 26 April 2015
cid.title_ar: هجوم كيماوي على قرية جوزف جبل الزاوية في ادلب ٢٦ ابريل ٢٠١٥

summary_en: I was unable to find any reports or Youtube videos about a chemical attack on Marjeh on 26 April 2015. I searched using various different spellings of Marjeh in English, as well as searched in Arabic (المرجة، مرجة) with no luck. There were also no videos on the Master spreadsheet.

Not a lot of media about incident. Reports suggest that government helicopters allegedly dropped at least 2 barrel bombs containing chlorine on Saraqeb in Idlib. Around 12 people, including children, were injured and suffered from suffocation. One video shows a news report about the incident. Another video shows the Idlib Civil Defense Team walking around ruined buildings, collecting samples and documenting the chemical attack.
cid.title_en: Chemical attack in Saraqeb, Idlib 29 April 2015
